SIMPLE: ungulate
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ungulate
<hw>Un"gu*late</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ungulatus</ets>. See <er>Ungula</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Shaped like a hoof.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Furnished with hoofs. See the
Note under <er>Nail</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, 1.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ungulate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Ungulate
<hw>Un"gu*late</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any hoofed
quadruped; one of the Ungulata.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unguled</ent>⟦br⟧
